Coquitlam.name: Town Centre Park
Coquitlam.description: Town Centre Park is a large urban park in the heart of Coquitlam, British Columbia. It offers a variety of recreational activities, including sports fields, walking trails, a lake, and picnic areas.

Coquitlam.name: Minnekhada Regional Park
Coquitlam.description: Minnekhada Regional Park is a large nature park located in Coquitlam, British Columbia. It features scenic hiking trails, wildlife viewing areas, and a historic lodge.
Coquitlam.opening_hours: 7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m. (April to September); 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. (October to March)

Burnaby.name: Dr. Sun Yat-Sen Classical Chinese Garden
Burnaby.description: The Dr. Sun Yat-Sen Classical Chinese Garden is a Chinese garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. Located in the city's Chinatown, it was the first Chinese garden built outside of Asia.
Burnaby.exact_location: 578 Carrall Street Vancouver, British Columbia V6B 5K2 Canada

Burnaby.name: Central Park
Burnaby.description: Just minutes from Burnaby's largest shopping complex, this urban forest features winding paths, quiet ponds and beautiful gardens–not to mention lively areas for special events, sports and games.
Burnaby.exact_location: 4949 Canada Way, Burnaby BC Canada, V5G 1M2

Burnaby.name: Deer Lake Park
Burnaby.description: To the north of Deer Lake, you'll find Burnaby's cultural centre–Burnaby Art Gallery, Shadbolt Centre for the Arts, Burnaby Village Museum and more. It's a hub of activity during the busy summer season, hosting concerts and festivals on the Festival Lawn.

Burnaby.name: Burnaby Mountain Park
Burnaby.description: Burnaby Mountain Conservation Area isn't just a park, it's an area designated to protect forests, wetlands, plant life, wildlife and water.

Burnaby.name: Barnet Marine Park
Burnaby.description: Located on an important harvesting, gathering and processing site for the Coast Salish peoples, as well as the site of a century-old logging mill camp, echoes of the past add a rich sense of history to this spectacular foreshore park with ocean and mountain views.

Burnaby.name: Kensington Park
Burnaby.description: Kensington is sports central in the heart of north Burnaby. It offers everything for residents, schools and visitors–ice sports, field sports, racquet games, outdoor swimming and lots of areas to just play.

Burnaby.name: Burnaby Fraser Foreshore Park
Burnaby.description: Located on the north arm of the mighty Fraser, our riverfront park is home to meadows, marshes, creeks and animal habitats.

Burnaby.name: Confederation Park
Burnaby.description: Picnic under the trees, ride the model steam train, catch some air in the skateboard plaza, cool off in the spray park or explore the rugged north side of the park.
